🔷 CommonJS Module System

Node.js traditionally uses **CommonJS modules**.

Import:

```javascript
const module = require("module");
```

Export:

```javascript
module.exports = value;
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 ES Modules (Modern JavaScript)

Modern Node.js supports **ES Modules**.

Import:

```javascript
import express from "express";
```

Export:

```javascript
export default function greet() {
  console.log("Hello");
}
```

Enable ES Modules:

Add to `package.json`:

```json
{
  "type": "module"
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 require() Function

`require()` loads modules.

Example:

```javascript
const fs = require("fs");
```

Node.js searches in:

1️⃣ Core modules
2️⃣ Local files
3️⃣ node_modules folder

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Module Wrapper

Node.js wraps modules inside a function.

Example:

```javascript
(function (exports, require, module, __filename, __dirname) {
  // module code
});
```

Useful variables:

| Variable   | Description    |
| ---------- | -------------- |
| __dirname  | Directory path |
| __filename | File path      |

Example:

```javascript
console.log(__dirname);
console.log(__filename);
```

